			<h3 style="text-align:center">7. Return of the Blossoming Blade (alt: Return of the Mount Hua Sect)</h3>
			<p>Chung Myung, the Plum Blossom Sword Saint, finds himself dying on the battlefield after killing the demon Chun Ma. However, he is reincarnated in a beggar child's body 100 years after he died against Chun Ma. What surprises the master of the blade is that the Mount Hua Sect, whose swordsmanship was recognized by Chun Ma as the strongest, is not even one of the top Twelve Sects. This story revolves around the reincarnated Chung Myung's efforts in restoring the Mount Hua Sect to its former glory.</p>
			<p>This manhwa is known for the protagonist's seemingly two-faced behaviour and comedic expressions throughout the story, be it 'charming' his brothers into becoming stronger, or ripping off a merchant using his skills (mild spoilers; harmless without context)</p>
